locality: Northern Tablelands. S side of Gwydir Hwy, 64 4km ENE of Glen Innes in Gibraltar Range National Park. In low heathy woodland with Eucalyptus sp. (fibrous bark), Leptospermum sp., Persoonia, Mirbelia confertifolia, Xanthorrhoea, Acacia, Dillwynia rupestris, Comesperma, Grevillea acerata, Boronia anethifolia & Allocasuarina. Shallow gravelly yellow sand with granite outcrops and pavement on upper slopes of hill.
About 35 miles [56 km] from Glen Innes, north east, near the Gwydir Highway.
